sections.body:
Consider a streaming data source that generates detailed weather
reports from various locations. In the following example aggregation
pipeline, you include a [$validate](pipe.$validate) stage to ensure the
documents conform to the schema of the [Sample Weather Dataset](sample-weather). The aggregation has four stages:

- The [$source](pipe.$source) stage establishes a connection with the
  [Apache Kafka](https://kafka.apache.org/) broker collecting these reports in a topic named
  `my_weatherdata`, passing each record as it is ingested to the
  subsequent aggregation stages.

- The [$validate](pipe.$validate) stage checks whether a document has array
  values for the `position.coordinates` and `sections` fields,
  passing documents that do to the rest of the pipeline, and passing
  documents that don't to a [Dead Letter Queue](atlas-sp-dlq).

- The [$match](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/match) stage excludes documents that have a
  `wind.speed.rate` value of greater than or equal to `30` and
  passes along the documents with a `wind.speed.rate` value of less
  than `30`.

- The [$merge](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/merge) stage writes the output to an Atlas
  collection named `stream` in the `sample_weatherstream`
  database. If no such database or collection exist, Atlas
  creates them.

```json
{
  '$source': {
    connectionName: 'sample_weatherdata',
    topic: 'my_weatherdata',
    tsFieldName: 'ingestionTime'
  }
},
{
  '$validate': {
    validator: {
      '$jsonSchema': { properties: { position: [Object], sections: [Object] } }
    },
    validationAction: 'dlq'
  }
},
{ '$match': { 'wind.speed.rate': { '$lt': 30 } } },
{
  '$merge': {
    into: {
      connectionName: 'weatherStreamOutput',
      db: 'sample_weatherstream',
      coll: 'stream'
    }
  }
}
```

To view the documents in the resulting `sample_weatherstream.sample`
collection, you can connect to your Atlas cluster using
[mongosh](mongodb-shell) to run the following command:

> **Note:** The following is a representative example. Streaming data are
> not static, and each user sees distinct documents.

**Input:**

```json
db.getSiblingDB("sample_weatherstream").stream.find()
```

**Output:**

```json
